    {
      "sellerId": "exshopi_official",
      "storeId": "exshopi_official",
      "categoryId": "cat1",
      "title": "AD-VISION SGS Certified Replacement Filters (6-Pack) for High Pressure Shower Head - Hard Water Softener Cartridge with Calcium Sulfite - Removes Chlorine, Rust & Sand to Prevent Hair Loss",
      "description": "Attention Please: To avoid purchasing the wrong product, please ensure you are ordering from our only store: NEXGEN FZE when placing your order. After receiving the goods, confirm that the packaging is consistent with the main product image; otherwise, the product you purchased is not from our company.\\nThis filter element is a special filter element for our double-sided shower head. Due to the differences in the length, thickness and interfaces at both ends of the filter element, please pay attention to purchasing the original filter element;\\nThe outer layer of this filter is made of very dense, tightly-wound PP cotton. Its mission is simple but crucial: to block harmful impurities, rust, and sediment. Please note: when you see the filter's color start to darken after a few days, it's not a quality problem with our filter. It's caused by the buildup of contaminants, and eventually, the entire filter will turn the color of mud.\\nDuring the disinfection process, water treatment plants add chlorine gas or chlorine compounds to kill bacteria and microorganisms. Although this is crucial for drinking water safety, the residual chlorine in the water when you shower (usually in the form of hypochlorous acid, HClO) can have some negative effects. The filter cartridge is a cylinder, and we have stuffed its hollow inner part full of chlorine removal balls. The advantage of Calcium Sulfite is its high efficiency in removing chlorine and its high-temperature resistance, making it very suitable for showerheads. These are specifically used to neutralize the residual chlorine in tap water, protecting your skin and hair.\\nTo improve quality, all the filters we sell are SGS certified to guarantee the quality. This filter cartridge has had basically no user complaints from its launch until now. First, our supply manufacturer is stable, and second, we maintain a reasonable purchasing price to ensure that quality will not be lowered due to excessive cost compression.\\nRegarding whether the water pressure will be lowered after adding the filter, first: we have done actual tests, and there is almost no difference in brand new condition. Second: if the outer layer of the filter accumulates too many filtered substances, it will indeed seriously affect the showerhead's water pressure. This is when you need to replace the filter.",
      "price": 36.5,
      "originalPrice": 36.5,
      "salePrice": 36.5,
      "image": "https://images-eu.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/I/71fQ8-rLzDL._AC_UL300_SR300",
      "images": [
        "https://images-eu.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/I/71fQ8-rLzDL._AC_UL300_SR300"
      ],
      "stock": 100,
      "rating": 0,
      "reviews": 0,
      "sku": "B0F92S4V7L",
      "specs": {
        "importMeta": {
          "source": "thunderbit",
          "asin": "B0F92S4V7L"
        },
        "attributes": {
          "brand": "AD VISION"
        },
        "raw": {
          "Product Name": "AD-VISION SGS Certified Replacement Filters (6-Pack) for High Pressure Shower Head - Hard Water Softener Cartridge with Calcium Sulfite - Removes Chlorine, Rust & Sand to Prevent Hair Loss",
          "Product URL": "https://www.amazon.ae/AD-VISION-Certified-Replacement-Filters-Pressure/dp/B0F92S4V7L/ref=zg_bs_g_home-improvement_d_sccl_3/000-0000000-0000000?psc=1",
          "Product Image": "https://images-eu.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/I/71fQ8-rLzDL._AC_UL300_SR300",
          "Price (AED)": "36.50",
          "Rating (Max 5)": "4.3",
          "Number of Ratings": "202",
          "Brand": "AD VISION",
          "Material": "Acrylonitrile Butadiene Styrene+304",
          "Color": "Refill - 6 Packs",
          "Product Dimensions": "28L x 9W centimeters",
          "Special Features": "Wall Mounted\nAD-VISION's exclusive Dual-Sided Multi-Function Spray Engine (on applicable models) integrates two or more distinct, expertly calibrated spa modes onto opposite faces of a single shower head. For instance, Side A might offer a powerful pulsating massage jet for muscle relief, while Side B delivers a wide rainfall or gentle mist for relaxation. A simple flip allows seamless switching, offering superior versatility and convenience beyond standard multi-mode shower heads.\nAD-VISION's proprietary Rotate-Press Dual-Action Flow Control system uniquely integrates stepless water pressure adjustment (from gentle trickle to powerful torrent via rotation) and instant flow pause/resume (complete water stop via press) into a single, intuitive knob/button. This advanced, integrated design offers unparalleled convenience and a customized shower experience, setting it apart from standard shower heads.\nHigh-pressure boost function: Micro nozzle technology increases water pressure by 200%, provides stronger water flow, and saves 30% of water consumption.\nOur AD-VISION shower heads feature an advanced composite filtration system, rigorously tested and certified by SGS Switzerland. Unlike basic filters, this proprietary system is specifically engineered to effectively remove up to 99% of residual chlorine, heavy metal ions, sediments, and other impurities, while also softening hard water. This commitment to certified water purity provides significant benefits for skin and hair health, especially in regions with challenging water quality.\nSelect AD-VISION premium models incorporate our proprietary Micro-Nano Bubble Rejuvenation Technology. This system generates millions of ultra-fine bubbles, far smaller than skin pores, creating an oxygen-rich, milk-like water flow. This unique, silky stream provides an exceptionally gentle yet deep cleanse, enhancing skin hydration and radiance for a luxurious, spa-grade skincare experience at home.",
          "About This Item": "Attention Please: To avoid purchasing the wrong product, please ensure you are ordering from our only store: NEXGEN FZE when placing your order. After receiving the goods, confirm that the packaging is consistent with the main product image; otherwise, the product you purchased is not from our company.\\nThis filter element is a special filter element for our double-sided shower head. Due to the differences in the length, thickness and interfaces at both ends of the filter element, please pay attention to purchasing the original filter element;\\nThe outer layer of this filter is made of very dense, tightly-wound PP cotton. Its mission is simple but crucial: to block harmful impurities, rust, and sediment. Please note: when you see the filter's color start to darken after a few days, it's not a quality problem with our filter. It's caused by the buildup of contaminants, and eventually, the entire filter will turn the color of mud.\\nDuring the disinfection process, water treatment plants add chlorine gas or chlorine compounds to kill bacteria and microorganisms. Although this is crucial for drinking water safety, the residual chlorine in the water when you shower (usually in the form of hypochlorous acid, HClO) can have some negative effects. The filter cartridge is a cylinder, and we have stuffed its hollow inner part full of chlorine removal balls. The advantage of Calcium Sulfite is its high efficiency in removing chlorine and its high-temperature resistance, making it very suitable for showerheads. These are specifically used to neutralize the residual chlorine in tap water, protecting your skin and hair.\\nTo improve quality, all the filters we sell are SGS certified to guarantee the quality. This filter cartridge has had basically no user complaints from its launch until now. First, our supply manufacturer is stable, and second, we maintain a reasonable purchasing price to ensure that quality will not be lowered due to excessive cost compression.\\nRegarding whether the water pressure will be lowered after adding the filter, first: we have done actual tests, and there is almost no difference in brand new condition. Second: if the outer layer of the filter accumulates too many filtered substances, it will indeed seriously affect the showerhead's water pressure. This is when you need to replace the filter.",
          "Date First Available": "05/18/25",
          "ASIN": "B0F92S4V7L"
        }
      },
