          "Special Features": "Bucket Storage",
          "About This Item": "EFFECTIVE DEHUMIDIFICATION: The CLEVAST dehumidifier boxes feature spherical calcium chloride particles that can attract and absorb excess moisture quickly and efficiently. Moisture absorbers are designed with premium one-way moisture-permeable paper that will securely lock the moisture inside.\\nEASY TO USE & STORAGE: No assembly is required. Each closet moisture absorber is stored in a separate box for easy use and long-term storage. These can be placed anywhere for physical dehumidification. They take up just a little space in your room and help to get rid of odor in your damp home.\\nVISIBLE DEHUMIDIFYING PROCESS: The CLEVAST absorber buckets absorb excess moisture from the air and collect it in the storage area, functioning like a small dehumidifier. The amount of water accumulated through the dehumidification process can be monitored at any time. With a large capacity of 280g per box, it lasts longer. (IF YOU NEED MORE POWERFUL DEHUMIDIFICATION, YOU CAN PEEL OFF THE WHITE PERMEABLE PAPER).\\nVERSATILE USAGE: Our safe humidity absorber boxes are suitable for most enclosed spaces, such as basement, kitchen, bathroom, car, garage, laundry room, warehouse, and caravan. Put it in the damp space where excess moisture is an issue. Then, you can enjoy a dry and comfortable indoor environment for a long time.\\nHow It Works: When using moisture eliminator boxes, the white calcium chloride dissolves and forms a whole piece, leading to water droplets appearing in 5-7 days. As dehumidification continues, more water will collect in the catchment area. In LOW humidity, transparent crystals may form in storage areas. Initial solidification of the dehumidifier can occur, but it will absorb moisture over time, turning into liquid(about 15-25 days). In HIGH humidity, all white calcium chloride will dissolve into pieces and become liquid about 3-7 days.",
